<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="26" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="26">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="26">
As stated above, this name is synonymous with 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Platythecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Platythecium dimorphodes" order="Ostropales" pageId="13" pageNumber="26" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimorphodes">Platythecium dimorphodes</taxonomicName>
(Nyl.) Staiger and unfortunately provides an earlier epithet for it.
</paragraph>
